Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: eb32e4584d8e9d6cbec20550d4f91396de2cdb55
Patch-mainline: 3.9-rc1
References: bnc#806406

Yet another remnant ... this might explain why l3 remapping didn't
really work on HSW.

Bugzilla: https://bugs.freedesktop.org/show_bug.cgi?id=57441
Spotted-by: Ville Syrjälä <ville.syrjala@linux.intel.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Reviewed-by: Ben Widawsky <ben@bwidawsk.net>
Signed-off-by: Daniel Vetter <daniel.vetter@ffwll.ch>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c
@@ -3852,7 +3852,7 @@ void i915_gem_l3_remap(struct drm_device
 	u32 misccpctl;
 	int i;
 
-	if (!IS_IVYBRIDGE(dev))
+	if (!HAS_L3_GPU_CACHE(dev))
 		return;
 
 	if (!dev_priv->l3_parity.remap_info)
